# Line-ending & content policy for the Goobers repo (#643).
#
# Goal: byte-identical, LF-normalized checkouts on Windows, macOS, and Linux, so
# a fresh clone never shows phantom whole-file CRLF diffs and never renormalizes
# a file whose bytes a test asserts verbatim.
#
# Scope: this governs the Goobers repo itself. Managed checkouts of *target*
# repos are pinned to core.autocrlf=false by the worktree layer
# (internal/worktree, see managedGitConfig); target repos are recommended to
# carry their own .gitattributes for the same guarantee.

# Default: let git detect text vs binary by content, and store + check out every
# text file with LF regardless of the host platform or the user's core.autocrlf.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Byte-asserted generated artifacts — golden fixtures and generated man pages are
# compared verbatim by CI (TestCLIDocsUpToDate and the *.golden guards). Mark
# them so git applies no conversion and the raw bytes are what round-trips.
*.golden -text
*.1 -text

# Binary assets: never treat as text.
*.png binary
